{"author":{"id":"783b610f274a0d93f6239db0fc75d0982606c877a4661d3aea84b42bc3a85cea"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1759950855,"nonce":"NqYh/Wp9okwE2nA34GOkKHNVAME=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOAW4Y0s7QabpF","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/7349","origin":"github"},"title":"Bug: PanTA requires element identifiers ending in \"gff\". Conflicts with new default \"Auto Build List\" defaults (strips extensions)","message":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/blob/c72f529206c3362a2e7ce97922ff3cefd88a8dab/tools/panta/panta.xml#L26-L27\n\nThis is probably to satisfy Roary requirements, but the standalone Roary tool was modified to handle the use case of element identifiers without the extra \".gff\" or dataset names that may include spaces. Could we change this tool to do the same thing?\n\nXRef: https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/pull/2546\n\nIn short, remove spaces and add in a \".gff\" to whatever the original sample name is (dataset file or collection element).\n\nReported at https://help.galaxyproject.org/t/panaroo-panta-sample-recognition-troubleshooting/16367/2\n\nTesting history showing both use cases with tool test 1 data -\u003e https://usegalaxy.eu/u/jenj/h/test-panta\n\n\u003e **Workaround for end-users**\n\u003e 1. Name your collection's element identifers like this: `sample.gff`\n\u003e    * all one term\n\u003e    * no spaces\n\u003e    * ending with a `.gff` \n\u003e 2. Not sure how to check your element identifiers or modify them? See this topic at the forum https://help.galaxyproject.org/t/panaroo-error-missing-dependancies/16207/6 and search our tutorials with the keyword \"collection\" for more!","files":null}]}